<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-676-990  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 676 990.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Sept 18 1989 v8 n19 p29(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Pub. Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fiber-optic card has transceiver. (Zenith Electronics Corp.andO;design) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Olsen, Florence.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Zenith Electronics Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    ZE.andO;Product:   Zenith Electronics FiberStar (Local area network) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFiber opticsNetworksCommunications Boards-CardsTransceivers (Computer Networks)Security.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Fiber-Optic Card Has TransceiverandM;Zenith Electronics Corp. officials said the company's new fiber-optic networkcard's internal transceiver design makes sense for security-sensitivegovernment installations, especially those requiring protection fromelectromagnetic interference.andM;&quot;If you want to do Tempesting, having the fiber-optic transceiver on the cardgives you significant advantages,&quot; said Semir Sirazi, general manager ofZenith's Communications Products group.andP;  The $895 transceiver-on-the-cardfits inside the standard IBM or IBM-compatible AT, XT or PC computer.andM;Some manufacturers' fiber-to-desktop connections are external &quot;two- orthree-piece solutions with a lot of cabling&quot; and are difficult to makeTempest-secure, he said.andP;  Zenith plans to make a Tempest version of itsfiber-optic network card, which fits into each network workstation connectedby fiber-optic cable, he said.andM;The card and other components of Zenith's FiberStar local area network systemcan be set up several ways, Sirazi said.andP;  They can be configured as a10-megabit/sec Ethernet departmental LAN or as a 10-megabit/sec Ethernetbackbone.andP;  The system also permits redundant, or fault-tolerant,configurations, Sirazi said.andP;  &quot;Hardware redundancy [two network cards] onyour workstation is permittable,&quot; he said.andM;Each Z-LAN10F FiberStar system consists of a network/transceiver card withdual-ported RAM, an eight-port or 14-port hub coupler, and an externaltransceiver with a standard AUI interface for bridging to existing coax ortwisted-pair Ethernet segments.andM;Government Technology Services Inc., Chantilly, Va., and other federalresellers sell the Z-LAN products, including the Z-LAN10F FiberStar system.andO;Zenith also makes a series of Z-LAN4000 broadband and Z-LAN10E baseband andtwisted-pair Ethernet networks.andM;The FiberStar system list prices are $895 for the network/transceiver card,$4,175 for the eight-port hub, $5,975 for the 14-port hub, and $595 for theexternal AUI transceiver.andM;Contact Semir Sirazi, Zenith Communications Products, tel.andP;  312-391-8000.andO;</TEXT></DOC>